md:
giải nghĩa từ "concurrence" sang tiếng việt; đưa ra nghĩa tiếng việt theo từ loại và đưa ra câu ví dụ, các từ liên quan và các từ trái nghĩa.

* Concurrence (noun) 
	+ Meaning: The act of happening or existing at the same time.
	+ Vietnamese: Sự trùng hợp thời gian.
	+ Example: The concurrence of the two events led to a major crisis.
	+ Related words: coincidence, synchrony, simultaneousness.
	+ Antonyms: non-coincidence, non-simultaneity.

* Concurrence (noun) 
	+ Meaning: The state of being in agreement or harmony.
	+ Vietnamese: Sự đồng thuận.
	+ Example: The concurrence of the two parties led to a successful negotiation.
	+ Related words: agreement, harmony, consensus.
	+ Antonyms: disagreement, discord, conflict.

* Concurrence (noun) 
	+ Meaning: The simultaneous occurrence of two or more things.
	+ Vietnamese: Sự trùng hợp.
	+ Example: The concurrence of the full moon and the high tide caused a flood.
	+ Related words: coincidence, synchrony, simultaneousness.
	+ Antonyms: non-coincidence, non-simultaneity.

Note: The meanings of "concurrence" can vary depending on the context in which it is used.
